{"id": "chunk_00036", "text": "# FILE: Full-Time-Staff-Turnover-Analysis.pptx # CATEGORY: Recruitment & Turnover # SIZE: 1953370 bytes ### Slide 1 Full-Time Staff Turnover Analysis SGH - RIYADH ### Slide 2 Overall Turnover Total Separations 165 employees Across all departments and tenure brackets Composition Split 120 voluntary (72.7%) 45 involuntary (27.3%) Overall Rate 13.75% Near acceptable range; target ≤12% through focused interventions 10% Voluntary Rate Within healthcare target range (10–12%) 3.75% Involuntary Rate Reflects performance controls and stability ### Slide 3 Monthly Exit Trend: April Spike The monthly departure figures through October 2025 are as follows: A spike of 27 exits in April 2025 significantly deviates from baseline. The total departures from January to October are 165.", "metadata": {"source": "Full-Time-Staff-Turnover-Analysis.pptx", "category": "Recruitment & Turnover", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00037", "text": "ril 2025 significantly deviates from baseline. The total departures from January to October are 165. We will investigate contract cycles, scheduling, and policy changes to understand this trend. ### Slide 4 High-Risk Areas Requiring Immediate Attention New Hire Turnover Many new employees leave within their first year, suggesting issues with training or unclear job roles. High-Turnover Teams A few key departments have very high turnover, needing special plans to keep staff. Pay Issues Our pay for important jobs isn't competitive, causing staff to leave for other companies. ### Slide 5 Strategic Priorities for Retention 01 Reduce Turnover Strengthen onboarding & job previews. 02 Enhance Compensation Competitiveness Competitive pay, allowances, & flexible benefits.", "metadata": {"source": "Full-Time-Staff-Turnover-Analysis.pptx", "category": "Recruitment & Turnover", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00038", "text": "previews. 02 Enhance Compensation Competitiveness Competitive pay, allowances, & flexible benefits. 03 Create Clear Career Pathways Transparent promotion & internal mobility. 04 Optimise Scheduling Practices Intelligent rostering to reduce burnout. 05 Strengthen Front-Line Leadership Train managers on feedback, equity, & retention KPIs. ### Slide 6 Voluntary vs Involuntary Breakdown Voluntary Involuntary 72.7% Voluntary Exits Due to pay, career growth, scheduling, and leadership issues. 27.3% Involuntary Exits Primarily performance-related terminations. ### Slide 7 Recommended Dashboard KPIs 1 Voluntary Turnover Monthly & Year-to-Date for clinical and non-clinical staff. 2 Early Exits Percentage of staff leaving within 6 and 12 months.", "metadata": {"source": "Full-Time-Staff-Turnover-Analysis.pptx", "category": "Recruitment & Turnover", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00039", "text": "r clinical and non-clinical staff. 2 Early Exits Percentage of staff leaving within 6 and 12 months. 3 Top 5 Departments with Exits Departments with high turnover, including action plan status. 4 Key Exit Reasons Common reasons for leaving: pay, career, scheduling, and management. 5 Offer Acceptance Success rate for external hires and internal promotions. ### Slide 8 Next Steps: Retention Governance Monthly Review Hold monthly meetings to review retention using dashboard and early warning signs. Department Action Plans Create action plans for the 5 departments with the most turnover, setting clear goals. Track & Adjust Watch key indicators (like pay equity, manager changes, and scheduling issues) and make quick adjustments.", "metadata": {"source": "Full-Time-Staff-Turnover-Analysis.pptx", "category": "Recruitment & Turnover", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00040", "text": "key indicators (like pay equity, manager changes, and scheduling issues) and make quick adjustments. Our Goal: Lower overall staff turnover to 12% or less within a year, using smart, data-backed retention efforts.", "metadata": {"source": "Full-Time-Staff-Turnover-Analysis.pptx", "category": "Recruitment & Turnover", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00041", "text": "wer overall staff turnover to 12% or less within a year, using smart, data-backed retention efforts.", "metadata": {"source": "Full-Time-Staff-Turnover-Analysis.pptx", "category": "Recruitment & Turnover", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
