{"id": "chunk_00058", "text": "# FILE: PT competency 1.xls # CATEGORY: Training & Competency # SIZE: 211456 bytes ### Sheet: Sheet2 SAUDI GERMAN HOSPITAL – Asser PHYSIOTHERAPY DEPARTMENT COMPETENCY Employee Name : Samar Mohamed Farouk Position : OPD physiotherapist Competency Program: | Competent | Remarks/ Yes | No | N/A | Recommendations: [Sample row, 3 cols]: A | [name] | Yes B | Fire and safety (PASS) | Yes C | Hazmat and Hazcom Hospital Codes and MSDS | Yes D | Infection Control (hand hygiene) | Yes E | general competencies for physiotherapist: | Yes 1) BLS certified | Yes 2) Assist the attending physician /surgeon in determining appropriate physical therapy | Yes 3) Reviews and evaluates patient records | Yes 4) Recommends the most appropriate physical therpay for specific disabilities | Yes 5) Schedules,performs", "metadata": {"source": "PT competency 1.xls", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00059", "text": "ommends the most appropriate physical therpay for specific disabilities | Yes 5) Schedules,performs and evaluates patient tests | Yes 6) Submits a written physical therapy program to the physician /surgeon for concurrence | Yes 7) Administers precise manual manipulation and massage techniques on affected part | Yes 8) Directs preparation of prothetic device and instructs patient of its use | Yes 9) Records and evaluates patient response and discusses progress with the physician | Yes 10)Recommends changes and advises when the patient is ready for discharge | Yes 11)Demonstrates proper physical therapy procedures for handicapped patients | Yes 12)Imparts physical therapy health-teachings for home care program | Yes 13)Responses to emergencies in hospital with out delay during on-call duty |", "metadata": {"source": "PT competency 1.xls", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00060", "text": "home care program | Yes 13)Responses to emergencies in hospital with out delay during on-call duty | Yes 14)Provides contiuing education and training in collaboration with academic affairs | Yes 15) Verbal & telephone orders | Yes 16) Knowledge to perform inventory | Yes 17)Atends to work and on-call schedules on time and finishs duties before duty end | Yes 18)Endorses to the next shift any uncompleted tasks to be contiued | Yes 19)Attends to scheduled or unscheduled meeting to disscus and resolve problems | Yes 20)Assists the chief of department like assuming administrative responsibility | Yes 21)Online use of hospital information access and hospital policies and procedures | Yes 1) Knowledge of FOCUS PDCA | Yes 2) Knowledge of departmental manual | Yes 3) Participating in continuous tr", "metadata": {"source": "PT competency 1.xls", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00061", "text": "edge of FOCUS PDCA | Yes 2) Knowledge of departmental manual | Yes 3) Participating in continuous training/education program and credit hours | Yes 4) Reporting of OVR | Yes 5) Reporting about the fall risk screening | Yes 6) Participating in TQM programs in collaboration with TQM | Yes G | Competency for ICU physiotherapist: | Yes | No | N/A | Remarks/Recommendation: 1) Inpatient computer module | N/A 2) Automatic stop order policy | N/A 3)Capability to evaluate all critical patients with treating doctors | N/A 4)Ability to set measurable goals for ICU patients and submit suitable care plan | N/A 5)Being oriented about importance of early mobilization for ICU patients | N/A 6)Orientation about the importance of prevention of deformities by using splinting | N/A 7)Awareness of importance o", "metadata": {"source": "PT competency 1.xls", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00062", "text": "out the importance of prevention of deformities by using splinting | N/A 7)Awareness of importance of on time documentation of all critical patients | N/A H | Competency of OUT- patient physiotherapist: | Yes | No | N/A | Remarks/Recommendation: 1)Capability to assess and reassess all varities of out patients and submit their care plans | Yes 2)Ability to set measurable goals for all out patients and record all in patient records | Yes 3)Ability to communicate in right way with patients and relatives and educate about home program | Yes 4)Caring and satisfaying the patients through applying all physiotherapy modalities | Yes 5)Implementing all needed safety measures for all PT equipments and arrange all tools | Yes I | Competency of pediatric physiotherapist : | Yes | No | N/A | Remarks/Re", "metadata": {"source": "PT competency 1.xls", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00063", "text": "arrange all tools | Yes I | Competency of pediatric physiotherapist : | Yes | No | N/A | Remarks/Recommendation: 1)Capability to assess and reassess pediatric cases either out or admitted | N/A 2)Ability to set measurable goals for cerebral palsy and implement suitable care plan | N/A 3)Ability to communicate with parents and educate them home program of handicapped | N/A 4)Caring the pediatric rehabilitation unit and arrange all tools at end of day | N/A 5)Awareness of importance of scheduling of all kids to avoid any disturbance | N/A 6)Make sure of implementation of all infection control measures | N/A J | Competency of WARD physiotherapist: | Yes | No | N/A | Remarks/Recommendation: 1) Inpatient computer module | N/A 2) Automatic stop order policy | N/A 3)Capability to evaluate all ad", "metadata": {"source": "PT competency 1.xls", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
