{"id": "chunk_00093", "text": "# FILE: TNA Interview Template (005) (1).pdf # CATEGORY: Training & Competency # SIZE: 434541 bytes ### Page 1 SGH Structured Interview Guide – Training Needs Assessment (2025) (For use with CMO, CNO, Nurse Educator, PX Manager, HRBP) Section 1: Interviewee Information Branch Department Interviewee Name Job Title Interview Date Interviewer Name Section 2: Organizational Alignment 1. What are the key challenges your department is facing in achieving SGH’s strategic objectives? 2. What new trends in healthcare or competition in your region might require new skills or behaviors from your staff? 3.", "metadata": {"source": "TNA Interview Template (005) (1).pdf", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00094", "text": "n healthcare or competition in your region might require new skills or behaviors from your staff? 3. What are specific features or operational characteristics that distinguish your branch from others? (e.g., location, case types, staff mix, community demographics, etc.) Section 3: Competency -Based Questions A. Core Competencies 3. What are recurring behavioral issues or gaps you’ve observed in your team related to SGH’s core competencies (e.g., accountability, teamwork, communication , customer focus )? Please give examples. 4. Are there common performance issues raised in PX reports or patient complaints? B. Leadership Competencies (only if applicable) 5.", "metadata": {"source": "TNA Interview Template (005) (1).pdf", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00095", "text": "ssues raised in PX reports or patient complaints? B. Leadership Competencies (only if applicable) 5. What leadership gaps do you observe in team leads, coordinators, or managers in your department? (e.g., strategic thinking& planning, delegation, feedback, conflict handling) 6. Are there competency areas that managers consistently struggle with during department rounds or escalations? ### Page 2 Section 4: Data -Driven Inputs 7. Have recent performance appraisals highlighted any trends in staff development needs (especially those rated as “meeting” or “below expectations”)? 8. What training have team members in your division already attended this year? Was it effective? Section 5: Recommendations 9. What specific training topics do you believe are needed for your team? 10.", "metadata": {"source": "TNA Interview Template (005) (1).pdf", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00096", "text": "ion 5: Recommendations 9. What specific training topics do you believe are needed for your team? 10. Are there specific roles or staff categories that should be prioritized for training? Section 6: Logistics & Preferences 11. What is your preferred training format for your staff? - ☐ In-person - ☐ Virtual (live) - ☐ Recorded/On -demand - ☐ Blended - ☐ Coaching/Mentoring 12. What is the ideal duration of training per session/day to maximize engagement and retention? (e.g., 2 hours/day, half -day workshop, full day, etc.) 13. Any preferred time of day or week to schedule training for your staff? (e.g., Early morning, post -shift, Thursdays, etc.) Section 7: Notes & Additional Suggestions _Use this space to capture additional comments, pain points, or ideas shared by the interviewee._", "metadata": {"source": "TNA Interview Template (005) (1).pdf", "category": "Training & Competency", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
