{"id": "chunk_00143", "text": "# FILE: BP Form 2026 manal.pptx # CATEGORY: Business Planning # SIZE: 3810323 bytes ### Slide 1 Saudi German Health Business Plan 2026 ### Slide 2 SWOT Analysis POSITIVE NEGATIVE EXTERNAL INTERNAL STRENGTH WEAKNESS OPPORTUNITY THREAT • Strong HR team expertise in policies and procedures. • Proven experience in managing seasonal recruitment (such as Hajj). • Good relations with official authorities (Qiwa – Ajeer – Ministry of Human Resources). • High commitment to compliance with labor laws and regulations. • Some processes are still manual and time-consuming. • Limited structured employee development framework. • Delays in job evaluations and job descriptions. • Government Saudization initiatives. • Possibility of establishing training partnerships with universities and institutes.", "metadata": {"source": "BP Form 2026 manal.pptx", "category": "Business Planning", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00144", "text": "n initiatives. • Possibility of establishing training partnerships with universities and institutes. • Growing awareness of the importance of employee happiness and retention. • Strong competition in attracting medical and administrative talents. • Frequent changes in labor regulations impacting recruitment and workforce stability. • Rising recruitment and salary costs. • Risk of losing talents to competing hospitals. ### Slide 3 3 ### Slide 4 Detailed Objectives and Initiatives (2026) 4 No | Pilars | Objectives | Initaitives / Action | TimeLine [Sample row, 4 cols]: [N] | [name] | - Optimize manpower cost mix w | 1. Hiring based on replacement 3.", "metadata": {"source": "BP Form 2026 manal.pptx", "category": "Business Planning", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00145", "text": "mple row, 4 cols]: [N] | [name] | - Optimize manpower cost mix w | 1. Hiring based on replacement 3. Prioritize Saudi Hiring to maximize HRDF utilization | Q1-Q3 3 | Enhance Sub-Specialty | - Ensure full coverage of required sub-specialty physicians in alignment with the approved 2026 manpower plan, while strengthening retention. | 1.Hiring based on the quarter set on the manpower plan and needs. | Q2 2.Ensure all the staff have active accounts and participate on the mandatory training programs | Q1-Q4 2.Reduce Paper based transactions | Q1-Q4 ### Slide 5 5 Revenue Mix [Sample row, 7 cols]: No | Initiatives | [name] | Measures / KPIs | Target | [name] | Progress 1 | Hiring based on replacement & needed manpower based on workload analysis and utilization.", "metadata": {"source": "BP Form 2026 manal.pptx", "category": "Business Planning", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
{"id": "chunk_00146", "text": "ogress 1 | Hiring based on replacement & needed manpower based on workload analysis and utilization. | HR | Staff cost vs Budget | Approved HR budget | Q1 | Planned ### Slide 6 6 Improve Patient Journey [Sample row, 7 cols]: No | Initiatives | [name] | Measures / KPIs | Target | [name] | Progress 1 | Implement a 2026 Training plan based on patient journey and service gaps | HR | • Number of frontline staff trained • Training completion rate | ≥ 90% of targeted staff trained | Q1-Q4 | Planned 2 | Soft Skills and Patient Experience Training | HR | • Patient Experience (PX) score • Patient satisfaction trend | 100% of eligible staff evaluated | Q2 | Planned 4 | “Caring Like Family” as a core value | HR | • Employee engagement score ### Slide 7 7 Enhance Sub-Specialty [Sample row, 7 cols]: No", "metadata": {"source": "BP Form 2026 manal.pptx", "category": "Business Planning", "owner": "Mohamed Fekri Soliman", "pii_status": "anonymized"}}
